# mydefs for examples/textbook.md
#
# Defines @Theorem, @Lemma, @Proof labelled result blocks.  See
# cookbook recipe #31.
#
# Note: mydefs is included before @BasicSetup is in scope, so the
# high-level shortcuts @B / @I / @LP are not yet defined here.  Use
# the underlying primitives directly.

# @Theorem / @Lemma:  bold "Theorem." or "Lemma." label, then the
# statement set in italic (slope) so it stands apart from the
# surrounding roman body.  A non-breaking space (~) gives a small
# gap between the label and the statement.
def @Theorem right body
{
  { Bold @Font { Theorem.~ } } { Slope @Font body }
}

def @Lemma right body
{
  { Bold @Font { Lemma.~ } } { Slope @Font body }
}

# @Proof:  italic "Proof." label, then the body in the surrounding
# roman font, with a trailing small open-box as the qed marker.
def @Proof right body
{
  { Slope @Font { Proof.~ } } body ~ {Bold @Font "[]"}
}
